Teemo_test_rule2: 2. In this test, the transactions and liquidity pools both require using mainnet tokens. However, the profit or loss made by the transaction or liquidity pool will not actually affect your principal. Data will be recorded for subsequent function improvement, as well as testing credits calculation based on certain rules only.
Teemo_test_rule3: Note: The handling fee charged for opening a position will be used to feed the market price and will not be refunded after closing
Teemo_test_rule4: 3. Test credits can be converted into official tokens after the TEEMO project is officially launched
Teemo_test_rule5: Note: The test credits will not be credited to your wallet; the data will be bound to the wallet account you use
Teemo_test_rule6: 4. If you provide liquidity in the liquidity pool, please be sure to withdraw your pledged liquidity before XXXX. The withdrawal portal will be closed on XXXX.
Teemo_test_calculate_rule1: Every time a user opens a position, it counts as 0.1 point; every time a user closes a position, it counts according to the profit and loss of the order: for profitable trades, the points will be calculated based on the number of profits (1 point is counted for every 1BNB profit); for losing trades, no points will be counted.
Teemo_test_calculate_rule2: Each block is scored with 10 credits. Credits are allocated according to the proportion of funds pledged in the BNB liquidity pool at the time, points are allocated. The credits displayed on the page will be updated when you pledge or unlock the liquidity.
Notice_text1: for current test version, all P/L by tradings and liquidity pool will not be realized. During test, all the addresses, which provide liquidity and trades, will be rewarding points, which can convert to official token after project being launched.
